## 6. Station Management Implementation

### Rule 6.1: User Station Data Structure
- **ALWAYS** use nested structure for user stations: `userStation.station.name`
- **ALWAYS** use camelCase for frontend properties: `isDefault`, `stationId`
- **ALWAYS** transform flattened SQL results into nested objects
- **ALWAYS** include both user station and station data in response

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT User Station Structure
{
  id: number,
  user_id: number,
  station_id: number,
  isDefault: boolean,
  status: string,
  station: {
    id: number,
    name: string,
    status: string
  }
}

// ❌ WRONG - Flattened structure
{
  id: number,
  station_id: number,
  station_name: string,
  is_default: boolean
}
```

### Rule 6.2: Station Management API Endpoints
- **ALWAYS** support GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE methods for user stations
- **ALWAYS** use action-based routing for PATCH operations
- **ALWAYS** include proper permission checks for all operations
- **ALWAYS** return consistent data structures

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT API Endpoint Structure
if (req.method === "GET") {
  // Fetch user stations
}
if (req.method === "POST") {
  // Add station to user
}
if (req.method === "PATCH") {
  const { action } = req.body;
  if (action === "deactivate" || action === "activate") {
    // Toggle station status
  } else {
    // Set default station
  }
}
if (req.method === "DELETE") {
  // Remove station from user
}
```

### Rule 6.3: Station Management Frontend Implementation
- **ALWAYS** handle loading states for station operations
- **ALWAYS** validate user roles before allowing station assignment
- **ALWAYS** provide visual feedback for station status changes
- **ALWAYS** filter available stations to exclude already assigned ones
- **ALWAYS** use proper error handling for all station operations

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Station Management Pattern
const fetchUserStations = async (userId: number) => {
  setLoadingStations(true);
  setStationError("");
  try {
    const result = await apiCall(`/api/users/${userId}/stations`);
    if (result.status === 200) {
      setUserStations(result.data || []);
    } else {
      setStationError(result.error || "Failed to fetch user stations");
    }
  } catch (error) {
    setStationError("Network error occurred");
  } finally {
    setLoadingStations(false);
  }
};
```

### Rule 6.4: Role-Based Station Assignment
- **ALWAYS** restrict station assignment to sales, supervisor, and admin roles
- **ALWAYS** validate user role before allowing station operations
- **ALWAYS** provide clear error messages for unauthorized operations
- **ALWAYS** disable station management UI for unauthorized roles

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Role Validation
const allowedRoles = ["sales", "supervisor", "admin"];
const userRole = selectedUser.roles?.[0]?.name;

if (!userRole || !allowedRoles.includes(userRole)) {
  setStationError(`Only users with ${allowedRoles.join(", ")} roles can be assigned stations. Current role: ${userRole || "none"}`);
  return;
}
```

### Rule 6.5: Station Data Transformation
- **ALWAYS** transform SQL query results into expected frontend structure
- **ALWAYS** map database column names to frontend property names
- **ALWAYS** include both user station and station information
- **ALWAYS** handle null/undefined values gracefully

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Data Transformation
const results = await this.userStationRepository.query(query, [userId]);
return results.map((row: any) => ({
  id: row.id,
  user_id: row.user_id,
  station_id: row.station_id,
  isDefault: row.is_default,
  status: row.status,
  station: {
    id: row.station_id,
    name: row.station_name,
    status: row.station_status
  }
}));
```

### Rule 6.6: Station Management UI Components
- **ALWAYS** show loading states during station operations
- **ALWAYS** display station status with appropriate badges
- **ALWAYS** provide dropdown actions for each station
- **ALWAYS** show default station indicators
- **ALWAYS** handle empty states gracefully

```typescript
