## 8. Pricelist Switching Implementation

### Rule 8.1: Pricelist Context Usage
- **ALWAYS** use `PricelistContext` for managing pricelist selection in billing
- **ALWAYS** import: `import { usePricelist } from "../contexts/PricelistContext";`
- **ALWAYS** initialize: `const { currentPricelist, availablePricelists, setCurrentPricelist } = usePricelist();`
- **ALWAYS** wrap billing components with `PricelistProvider`

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Pricelist Context Usage
import { usePricelist } from "../contexts/PricelistContext";

const BillingComponent = () => {
  const { currentPricelist, availablePricelists, setCurrentPricelist } = usePricelist();
  
  // Use pricelist for item fetching
  const fetchItems = async (categoryId: string) => {
    if (!currentPricelist) return;
    
    const result = await apiCall(
      `/api/menu/items/pricelist?pricelistId=${currentPricelist.id}&categoryId=${categoryId}`
    );
    // Handle result...
  };
};
```

### Rule 8.2: Pricelist Switcher Component
- **ALWAYS** use `PricelistSwitcher` component for pricelist switching in billing
- **NEVER** use `StationSwitcher` in billing components
- **ALWAYS** provide `onPricelistChange` callback to refetch items
- **ALWAYS** show pricelist switcher only when multiple pricelists are available

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Pricelist Switcher Usage
<PricelistSwitcher 
  size="sm"
  showLabel={false}
  onPricelistChange={() => {
    // Refetch items when pricelist changes
    if (selectedCategory) {
      fetchItems(selectedCategory.id);
    }
  }}
/>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use StationSwitcher in billing
<StationSwitcher /> // WRONG!
```

### Rule 8.3: Item Fetching by Pricelist
- **ALWAYS** use `/api/menu/items/pricelist` endpoint for fetching items in billing
- **ALWAYS** pass `pricelistId` parameter instead of `stationId`
- **ALWAYS** validate user access to pricelist before fetching items
- **NEVER** use station-based item fetching in billing components

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Pricelist-based Item Fetching
const fetchItems = async (categoryId: string) => {
  if (!currentPricelist) {
    setItemError("No pricelist selected. Please select a pricelist first.");
    return;
  }

  const result = await apiCall(
    `/api/menu/items/pricelist?pricelistId=${currentPricelist.id}&categoryId=${categoryId}&userId=${userId}`
  );
  // Handle result...
};

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use station-based fetching in billing
const result = await apiCall(
  `/api/menu/items/station?stationId=${currentStation.id}&categoryId=${categoryId}`
); // WRONG!
```

### Rule 8.4: Station Switching Restrictions
- **ALWAYS** restrict station switching to admin/supervisor roles only
- **ALWAYS** hide `StationSwitcher` and `StationSelector` for sales/cashier users
- **ALWAYS** check user roles before showing station switching UI
- **ALWAYS** use pricelist switching for sales users instead of station switching

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Role-based Station Switching
const canSwitchStations = user?.roles?.some(role => 
  role.name === 'admin' || role.name === 'supervisor'
) || false;

if (!canSwitchStations) {
  return null; // Hide station switching UI
}

// ✅ CORRECT - Use pricelist switching for sales users
{userRole === 'sales' && (
  <PricelistSwitcher onPricelistChange={handlePricelistChange} />
)}
```

### Rule 8.5: Pricelist Access Validation
- **ALWAYS** validate user access to pricelists through their assigned stations
- **ALWAYS** check that pricelist is active and linked to user's stations
- **ALWAYS** return empty array if user doesn't have access to pricelist
- **ALWAYS** log access validation for debugging

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Pricelist Access Validation
private async validateUserPricelistAccess(userId: number, pricelistId: number): Promise<boolean> {
  const accessCheck = await userStationRepository
    .createQueryBuilder("us")
    .innerJoin("station_pricelist", "sp", "sp.station_id = us.station_id")
    .where("us.user_id = :userId", { userId })
    .andWhere("us.status = :status", { status: "active" })
    .andWhere("sp.pricelist_id = :pricelistId", { pricelistId })
    .andWhere("sp.status = :pricelistStatus", { pricelistStatus: "active" })
    .getCount();

  return accessCheck > 0;
}
```

### Rule 8.6: Pricelist Context Dependencies
- **ALWAYS** ensure `PricelistProvider` is wrapped around `StationProvider`
- **ALWAYS** refresh pricelists when station changes
- **ALWAYS** set default pricelist for current station
- **ALWAYS** handle pricelist loading states

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Context Hierarchy
<AuthProvider>
  <StationProvider>
    <PricelistProvider>
      {children}
    </PricelistProvider>
  </StationProvider>
</AuthProvider>

// ✅ CORRECT Pricelist Refresh on Station Change
useEffect(() => {
  if (currentStation && isAuthenticated) {
    refreshPricelists();
  }
}, [currentStation, isAuthenticated, refreshPricelists]);
```

### Rule 8.7: Pricelist UI States
- **ALWAYS** show "No Pricelist Available" message when no pricelist is accessible
- **ALWAYS** show loading states during pricelist fetching
- **ALWAYS** handle pricelist switching errors gracefully
- **ALWAYS** provide clear feedback for pricelist operations

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Pricelist UI States
if (!currentPricelist) {
  return (
    <Alert variant="warning">
      <Alert.Heading>No Pricelist Available</Alert.Heading>
      <p>No pricelist is available for your current station. Please contact an administrator.</p>
    </Alert>
  );
}

// ✅ CORRECT Loading State
{isLoading && (
  <Spinner animation="border" size="sm" className="me-2" />
)}
```

### Rule 8.8: Pricelist Data Structure
- **ALWAYS** use consistent pricelist data structure across frontend and backend
- **ALWAYS** include station information in pricelist objects
- **ALWAYS** map database results to expected frontend format
- **ALWAYS** handle null/undefined values gracefully

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Pricelist Data Structure
interface Pricelist {
  id: number;
  name: string;
  status: string;
  is_default: boolean;
  description?: string;
  station?: {
    id: number;
    name: string;
  };
}

// ✅ CORRECT Data Transformation
pricelists = rawPricelists.map(row => ({
  id: row.pricelist_id,
  name: row.pricelist_name,
  status: row.pricelist_status,
  is_default: row.pricelist_is_default,
  description: row.pricelist_description,
  station: {
    id: row.station_id,
    name: row.station_name
  }
}));
```

Remember: Always use `useApiCall()` instead of raw fetch, handle HTTP response errors with standardized error states and ErrorDisplay components, use the correct layout for each user role, treat voiding and reopening as separate features with distinct workflows, permissions, and UI components, ensure proper data structure transformation for station management operations, maintain compatibility with main branch user management patterns, and implement pricelist switching for sales users while restricting station switching to admin/supervisor roles only.